	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I can't give you the answer, but if you have a multimeter you could check the ROM pins against the connector pins (I believe the pinout is also on the wiki). Most of the pins should be connected directly (lower address lines, VCC, data lines), and the ones that are not (higher address lines) should be connected to the mapper. Do we know the pinouts of these mappers? Anyway, I hope someone can give a straight answer, but if that doesn't happen and you got the board, you could test it yourself.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


